Wash and dry produce.

Halve, core, and thinly slice @bell pepper{1}(halved, cored, and thinly sliced into strips). Halve and peel @yellow onion{1}(peeled and halved); thinly slice one half.

Finely chop remaining onion until you have 1 TBSP (2 TBSP for 4 servings).

In a #small pot{}, combine @jasmine rice{1/2%cup}, 1 cup water (2 cups for 4 servings), and a pinch of @salt{pinch}.

Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce to a low simmer. Cook until rice is tender, ~{15-20%minutes}.

> TIP: If rice is al dente, add water 1 TBSP at a time until rice is tender or reaches desired texture.

Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

While rice cooks, heat a large drizzle of @cooking oil{4%tsp} in a #medium pan{} over medium-high heat.

Add bell pepper and sliced onion; cook, stirring occasionally, until slightly softened, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Add @shredded collard greens{3%oz}; cook, stirring, until slightly softened, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Stir in half the @chicken stock concentrate{2}, half the @hot sauce{1%tsp}, 1/4 cup water, @sugar{1%tsp}, and a pinch of salt and @pepper{pinch}.

(For 4 servings, use as much hot sauce as you like, 1⁄3 cup water, and 2 tsp sugar).

Cook, stirring constantly, until collards are wilted and liquid has evaporated, ~{3-5%minutes}.

> TIP: Prefer softer collard greens? Add another splash of water and cook 3-4 minutes more.

Turn off heat.

Pat @pork chops{10%oz} dry with #paper towels{}; place in a #medium bowl{}.

Season all over with @fry seasoning{1%tbsp}, half the @flour{2%tbsp}, @dried thyme{1%tsp}, @salt{} and @pepper{}; turn to coat.

Heat a drizzle of cooking oil in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat.

Add pork and cook until browned and cooked through, ~{4-5%minutes} per side.

Turn off heat; transfer to a #cutting board{} to rest. Wipe out pan.

Melt @butter{2%tbsp} in pan used for pork over medium heat.

Add chopped onion; cook, stirring, until softened and fragrant, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Add a drizzle of oil, remaining flour, and @dried thyme{1/4%tsp}; cook, stirring, until lightly browned, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Whisk in @beef stock concentrate{1}, remaining chicken stock concentrates, and 1 cup water (2 cups for 4). Simmer, whisking, until thickened, ~{3-5%minutes}.

Reduce heat to low. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{} to taste.

Fluff rice with a #fork{}; stir in @butter{1%tbsp} until melted. Season with salt to taste.

Slice pork crosswise.

Divide rice, pork, and veggies between #plates{}. Spoon gravy over pork and serve.